  "issue_title": "feature: add agent step model",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nMilestone 5 needs a shared representation for each local agent step before the loop and UI can evolve cleanly. Today, agent events and tool results exist, but the observe-decide-act loop does not have a compact step model that can be reused by the runner, tests, chat timeline, and run detail UI.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a structured agent step model for local runs. The model should represent step type, sequence number, status, input summary, output summary, tool call details when present, verification result when present, timestamps, and stop/clarification metadata.\n\nExpected step types include:\n\n- `observe`\n- `decide`\n- `act`\n- `verify`\n- `clarify`\n- `stop`\n\n## User workflow\n\nA user starts a local task and every internal step can later be rendered in chat or inspected in a run detail view.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis makes the local agent loop observable without relying on cloud traces or external debugging tools.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nStep fields must use existing redaction paths for tool args, screen text, and tool output. Sensitive data should not be persisted or rendered raw.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Adds a reusable step data model for local agent runs.\n- Covers observe, decide, act, verify, clarify, and stop steps.\n- Includes status and stop reason fields.\n- Keeps sensitive text redacted in display-facing fields.\n- Includes focused unit tests for model construction/serialization where applicable.",
